# Solar Tracking — Agent-first maintenance

## Before each session

1. Read `docs/FEATURES.md` → **Active phase** section
2. Read `AGENTS.md` for conventions and commands
3. Verify `.env` (local) or `.env.docker` (container) from `.env.example`
4. Run `pnpm run test` before invasive changes

## During work

- Work only on the phase/feature indicated in `FEATURES.md`
- Use absolute imports (`@/...`), TypeScript strict
- **UI text:** Italian | **Docs, README, TODO, rules, commits:** English
- Feature-based structure: `src/features/<name>/`
- Early return, minimal comments, small diffs
- Mock external services (Solarman, Telegram, LLM, weather)
- Do not expose the app on the network: bind `127.0.0.1` only
- **No hardcoded tunables** — use `getConfig()` from `app_config` (see `config-driven.mdc`)

## End of session

1. Update feature status in `docs/features/F*.md` and `docs/FEATURES.md`
2. Add a row to the **Handoff log** with a concrete next step
3. Run `pnpm run test` and `pnpm run build` if application code changed
4. Follow `commit-convention.mdc` when marking features complete

## Env and secrets

- `.env.example` — committed template
- `.env.local.example` — local dev template (host → MySQL on 127.0.0.1)
- `.env.docker` — Docker Compose variables (host → `mysql`)
- `.env` / `.env.local` — **never commit**, contain real credentials
- Tunables (intervals, thresholds) → `app_config` table via Settings UI

## Phases (do not skip)

| Phase | Scope |
|-------|-------|
| 0 | Bootstrap, Docker, env, tracking, base tests |
| 1 | Solarman sync → MySQL, checkpoint backfill |
| 2 | Dashboard + aggregates + battery history |
| 3 | Telegram + AI classification + battery alerts |
| 4 | Weather + forecast |

## First-time setup

See `docs/INIT.md` for clone → env → docker → backfill → settings → backup.

## Commands

```bash
docker compose up -d                        # base stack (app, worker, mysql)
docker compose --profile full up -d         # + llm, telegram-bot
docker compose --profile backup up -d       # + scheduled backup to Google Drive
pnpm run dev                                # local dev (outside Docker)
pnpm run test
pnpm run sync:once
pnpm run sync:backfill:full
pnpm run sync:worker
pnpm run db:dump
```
